## Step 5: QA

After generating, always run visual QA. See the QA section in [pptx SKILL.md](/mnt/skills/public/pptx/SKILL.md).

**Minimum checks:**
1. Extract text: `python -m markitdown output.pptx` — verify all content is present
2. Convert to images and inspect each slide visually
3. Confirm no text overflow, overlapping elements, or missing slides

---

## Slide Count Guidelines

| Deck Purpose | Recommended Slides |
|-------------|-------------------|
| Quick update / status | 5–7 |
| Standard business presentation | 8–12 |
| Investor / Pitch deck | 10–15 |
| Full proposal / report | 15–25 |
| Training module | 20–30 |

---

## Speaker Notes Best Practices

Add speaker notes to every content slide:
```javascript
slide.addNotes(`Key message: [what the speaker should emphasize]
Talking point 1: [supporting detail]
Talking point 2: [supporting detail]
Transition: [how to move to next slide]`);
```

---

## Output

Save the final file to `/Documents/presentation.pptx` and present it with `present_files`.

Always confirm to the user:
- Number of slides generated
- Color theme used
- Offer to adjust content, design, or add/remove slides